By Glory Abuh-Adejoh  Abuja   –      The National Industrial Court of Nigeria (NICN), will commence Christmas and New Year vacation from Monday, Dec. 17 and resume Friday, Jan. 4, 2019. The President of NICN, Justice Babatunde Adejumo, in a circular released on Monday in Abuja, said full judicial activities would commence on Jan. 7, 2019. He said the directive was in compliance with the provisions of Order 58, Rule 4 (1) (c) (Civil Procedure Rules), 2017 of the National Industrial Court of Nigeria. According to him, “during the Christmas and New Year vacation, there would not be court sittings, during the period of the vacation.”